# BYOK Cryptographic Vault

Canonical: `@src/lib/crypto.ts`, consumer `@src/contexts/SecureConfigContext.tsx`, `@SECURITY.md`.

## Algorithms

- **Encryption:** AES-256-GCM with unique IV per record.
- **KDF:** PBKDF2-HMAC-SHA256 at OWASP-recommended iteration count (600k+).
- Store `iv` and `salt` alongside ciphertext in Dexie `secureConfig`.

## Memory Lifecycle

- Derived keys and plaintext API secrets exist only transiently in memory.
- Wipe sensitive references on lock, timeout, or hard refresh.
- Never persist master password or raw keys to localStorage/sessionStorage.

<example>
const key = await deriveKey(masterPassword, salt);
const ciphertext = await encrypt(apiKey, key, iv);
await db.secureConfig.put({ provider, ciphertext, iv, salt });
</example>

<example type="invalid">
localStorage.setItem('openai_key', apiKey);
</example>

## Context API

- `SecureConfigContext` exposes lock/unlock and provider accessors — components must not import crypto primitives directly unless necessary.
- Decrypt only at the moment of an outbound API call; re-lock when idle if timeout is implemented.

## Logging & Tests

- Tests use known fixtures; never log real keys in test output.
- See `@src/lib/crypto.test.ts` for round-trip encrypt/decrypt patterns.
